{{Infobox book | name = Nuclear Nebraska | image = Nuclear Nebraska (book cover).jpg | caption = First edition cover | author = Susan Cragin | title_orig = | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = United States | language = English | series = | subject = [[Nuclear waste]] | genre = Non-fiction | publisher = American Management Association, New York | pub_date = 2007 | english_pub_date = | media_type = Print, e-book | pages = 271 pp. | isbn = 978-0-8144-7430-3 | oclc = 86172845 | dewey = | congress = | preceded_by = | followed_by = }}
'''''Nuclear Nebraska: The Remarkable Story of the Little County That Couldn’t Be Bought''''' is a 2007 book by [[Susan Cragin]] which follows the controversy about a proposed low level [[nuclear waste]] dump, which was planned for [[Boyd County, Nebraska]].<ref name=cragin>[http://world-wire.com/news/0711020001.html New AMACOM Book Chronicles the Story of One Community’s 18-Year Struggle with Big Government and Big Business] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071226133729/http://world-wire.com/news/0711020001.html |date=2007-12-26 }}</ref>
In 1989, two [[multinational corporations]] and several government agencies proposed a waste dump and offered payment of $3 million per year for 40 years. The residents of the Boyd County farming community resisted the offer and controversy followed for almost two decades. During this time, the community was transformed "from a small group of isolated farmers to a defiant band of environmentalists". The opposition of the community eventually succeeded, and the license to build the dump was denied.<ref name=cragin/>
Several governors became embroiled in the controversy, as well as legislators, bureaucrats and the community. One central figure went to jail and others were dismissed from their jobs. For many years, there was extensive coverage of the event by the [[news media]].<ref name=Moul2009>Francis Moul, "Review of Nuclear Nebraska", ''Great Plains Quarterly'', 1 January 2009.</ref>
U.S. Senator [[Ben Nelson]] wrote the foreword to the book.<ref name=Moul2009/>
